The management of national Insurance Commission (NAICOM) has disclosed that 2021 unaudited performance showed the sector’s Gross Premium Income (GPI) stood at N630,362.35 billion as against audited GPI of N514 billion recorded in the year 2020  According to the Rasaaq Salami, the Head, Corporate Communications and Market Development, NAICOM, the figures were derived from the quarterly reports submitted by the operators in 2021.  READ ALSO THIS: Insurance firms’ assets hit N2.09tn amidst recapitalisation suspension The statement further disclosed that total assets has risen to N2,139,203.39 trillion in 2021 while the industry paid a total of Net claims value N238,050.49billion to the policy holders in 2021. 